t color=#333333>(5/25/02 7:28:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8673.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Petition</span><hr size=1> I think what most people that visit this board tend to forget is that while there are many high level drops out there that, in most cases, have better stats than epic; those same high level drops AND epics are out of reach of a large percentage of the player base.  As the number of &quot;casual players&quot; reach their 50s and even 60 (which is probably something VI never intended- I seem to remember when kunark came out that it was announced that only the most die-hard eq player would ever reach 60) they naturally feel the desire to obtain some of the same items that the top tier guilds consider twink gear now - epics included.  As it stands VI now caters to the top tier guilds and it looks like the newest expansion is not going to be an exception ( I seriously doubt VI will make a LFG plane - so looks like that leaves the Plane of Knowledge or whatever for the casual gamer and we all know how many quests are complete-in-game with any expansion).  As more and better online RPGs are released IMO it will be the &quot;power-gamers&quot; that leave first or for good as they have done it all/seen it all and can afford to move on. Yes casual gamers will move on but by their very nature they will probably also continue to play EQ until they reach whatever goal they have in mind- it will just take a little longer now since their 2hours a night might go to another game for a few nights during the week.  To continue to enjoy the success that they have so far, VI needs to really start listening to the people that just don't have the time to camp items for multiple days.  Yes I know that this is perhaps a slap in the face to those of you that actually spent days/weeks/months to obtain and item (and i both respect and sympathize  you for enduring those camps) but not even the &quot;casual gamer&quot; wants to get to level60 while still using lamentations.  Sorry for the long ass post- probably more words posted today than in the almost three years that I have called The Nameless my home away from home.<br>
<br>
This post was in no means a flame towards anyone/any guild. Yes I have played the high end game some (even applied to one of the top guilds before RL intervened and made me take a hard look at the game. I may still play 8 hours or more a day but they are spent how I want to spend them thus I now consider myself a casual gamer).<br>
<br>
